ALES DATA\":\"Total sales data for each of the Bigton stores for a month can be visualized using a simple bar chart to present a single data series over multiple periods.\"", "\"PROPORTION OF REVENUE DATA\":\"The proportion of revenue earned by each product category for a month can be visualized using a pie chart to show the proportions for a single period.\"", "\"EVALUATING THE IMPACT OF ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING ON PRICING STRATEGIES AT BBB\":\"Brick By Brick (BBB) provides a range of building services, including garage conversions (GC) and extensions to properties (EX). BBB has a policy to price all jobs at budgeted total cost plus 50%. Overheads are currently absorbed on a labour hour basis. However, BBB has found that it has fewer GC contracts than expected, and it believes that this is because the current overhead absorption method apportions an excessive amount of overheads to GC, leading to a price that is uncompetitive. The company is now considering moving to an activity-based cost approach.\"", "\"ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING\":Activity-based costing (ABC) is a costing method that assigns overhead and indirect costs to related products and services by identifying cost drivers. This methodology involves identifying the activities within an organization and assigning the cost of each activity to all products and services based on their actual consumption. By doing so, ABC helps in more accurately tracing costs to products and services. The method allocates overheads to products based on activities that drive costs, such as machine setups, machine running, procurement, and delivery.", "\"CURRENT METHOD OF ABSORBING OVERHEADS\":\"The current method of absorbing overheads at BBB is based on labour hours.\"", "\"SALES PRICE FOR A TYPICAL GC USING CURRENT METHOD\":\"Price per unit using absorption cost plus 50%: Materials: $3,500, Labour (300 * 15): $4,500, Overheads (300 * ($400,000/40,000)): $3,000, Total cost: $11,000, Plus mark-up (50%): $5,500, Current price: $16,500.\"", "\"COST OF A GC USING ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING\":\"Cost per unit using activity-based costing: Materials: $3,500, Labour (300 * 15): $4,500, Overheads: Supervisors (1 * 180): $180, Planners (1 * 280): $280, Property related (300 * 6): $1,800, Total cost: $10,260.\"", "\"COST PER UNIT OF A TYPICAL EX USING ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING\":\"Cost per unit of a typical EX using activity-based costing: Materials: $8,000, Labour (500 * 15): $7,500, Overheads: Supervisors (6 * 180): $1,080, Planners (5 * 280): $1,400, Property related (500 * 6): $3,000, Total cost: $20,980, Therefore quoted price at 50% mark-up (20,980 * 150%): $31,470.\"", "\"QUIZ ON ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING AT BBB\":\"The quiz involves questions about the sales price for a typical GC using the current method of absorbing overheads, the cost of a GC using activity-based costing, the cost per unit of a typical EX using activity-based costing, and statements about the usefulness of activity-based costing and environmental activity-based costing.\"", "\"ENVIRONMENTAL LIFE-CYCLE COSTING\":\"Environmental life-cycle costing considers environmental costs from the design stage of a product through to decommissioning at the end of its life.\"", "\"EVALUATING COSTING METHODS FOR ACCURATE PROCEDURE PRICING AT BECKLEY HILL HOSPITAL\":\"Beckley Hill (BH) is a private hospital evaluating the implementation of activity-based costing (ABC) to more accurately price its procedures. The hospital currently uses a simple overhead allocation method but is considering ABC to better reflect the costs associated with different activities such as administrative time, nursing, catering, and general facility costs.\"", "\"LIFE-CYCLE COSTING ANALYSIS FOR NUCLEAR AND WIND POWER STATIONS AT VOLT CO\":\"Volt Co generates and sells electricity through nuclear and wind power stations. The case involves analyzing the life-cycle costs of these power stations, including operating costs, decommissioning costs, and the total life-cycle cost per gigawatt.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}